abstract: PHILADELPHIA, Sept. 28--The Montreal Expos made it two straight over the Philadelphia Phillies today and swept back into first place in the National League's Eastern Division with one week to play.

abstract: HOUSTON "HEY, Joe, what team are you  on?" Cesar Cedeno asked the question as Joe Morgan engaged a quintet of Cincinnati Reds around the batting cage last night, regaling them with the details of his three home runs on the Houston Astros' recent road trip.

abstract: PHILADELPHIA, Sept. 27--The Montreal Expos, fighting to stay alive in the race for the National League's Eastern title, revived mightily today to defeat Steve Carlton and the Philadelphia Phillies, 4-3, before 53,058 fans in Veterans Stadium.

abstract: Choate-Rosemary Hall and Phillips Exeter have not met many times on the football field, but yesterday's game at Exeter will long be remembered. Exeter lost a 23-20 heartbreaker when Choate intercepted a pass on its 30-yard line with 1:10 left.

abstract: The good news for Dobbs Ferry is that the Eagles shut out Hastings yesterday, 26-0, behind the brilliant running of Mo Sanginiti, but there was bad news for the school, too. Its star running back, Pete DeFilippis, injured his ankle and could be sidelined for several games.

abstract: A.C. Bostwick, a prominent amateur steeplechase rider in the United States and England and breeder-owner of the colt Mate, winner of the Preakness Stakes in 1931, died Friday at his home in Old Westbury, L.I. He was 79 years old.
